<h1>Test Cases and Benchmarks</h1>
Using --flags:test will include all source and configuration flagged as 'test' to allow using test and benchmark logic form a normally built application.

<h1>Options and Tasks of interest</h1>
<ul>
  <li>nop (option) - The No-Op option takes a list of task names not execute. For example if you are dealing with pure .java files, then issuing --nop:genJS will speed your build times.</li>
  <li></li>
</ul>

<h1>Additional Tooling</h1>
<h2>Project</h2>
<p>Project tooling provides a task for creating a new FOAM based project. It will create the default directory layout along with required poms.</p>
Usage:
<code>node foam3/tools/build.js -Ttemplate/demo/Project --createProject:net.foo</code>
<p>A fully functional <i>demo</i> can also be setup with the following.  The important bit is the subdomain <b>demo</b> at --createProject. With this the tooling will create an example model Demo along with all required journal configuration to deploy it.</p>
Example 1
<code>
  node foam3/tools/build.js -Ttemplate/demo/Project --createProject:com.foamdev.cook.recipe
  # then build with
  node foam3/tools/build.js deployment/demo/run.sh
  # login with demo user - username: demo, password: demopassword
  # or admin user - username: foam-admin, password: foam-admin
</code>
Example 2
<code>
  node foam3/tools/build.js -Ttemplate/demo/Project --createProject:net.foo.app.demo
  # then build with
  node foam3/tools/build.js deployment/demo/run.sh
  # login with demo user - username: demo, password: demopassword
  # or admin user - username: foam-admin, password: foam-admin
</code>
